Content provided by APO Group. CNBC Africa provides content from APO Group as a service to its readers, but does not edit the articles it publishes. CNBC Africa is not responsible for the content provided by APO Group. H.E. Ambassador, Mr. Richard A. Opembe, paid a courtesy call to Director General for International Trade and Investments, Ms. María Paz Ramos Resa, on 13th February 2020 at the State Secretariat for Trade offices in Madrid. During the visit, cordial discussions ranged from the current state of bilateral trade and investment relations to emerging opportunities.  Present in the meeting were Ms. Myriam Pérez Nogueira, the Deputy Director for Mediterranean Countries, Africa and Middle East, Mr. David Maina Kamau, Second Counsellor and Mr. Kamau Githure, the Commercial and Technical Services Asst. in the Embassy. Distributed by APO Group on behalf of Embassy of the Republic of Kenya in Spain.Media filesDownload logo